.TH wxFontPickerCtrl 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxFontPickerCtrl \- This control allows the user to select a font.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The generic implementation is a button which brings up a \fIwxFontDialog\fR when clicked. Native implementation may differ but this is usually a (small) widget which give access to the font-chooser dialog. It is only available if \fIwxUSE_FONTPICKERCTRL\fR is set to 1 (the default).

.SS "Styles"

.PP
This class supports the following styles:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFNTP_DEFAULT_STYLE: The default style: wxFNTP_FONTDESC_AS_LABEL | wxFNTP_USEFONT_FOR_LABEL.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFNTP_USE_TEXTCTRL: Creates a text control to the left of the picker button which is completely managed by the \fIwxFontPickerCtrl\fR and which can be used by the user to specify a font (see SetSelectedFont). The text control is automatically synchronized with button's value. Use functions defined in \fIwxPickerBase\fR to modify the text control.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFNTP_FONTDESC_AS_LABEL: Keeps the label of the button updated with the fontface name and the font size. E.g. choosing "Times New Roman bold, italic with size 10" from the fontdialog, will update the label (overwriting any previous label) with the "Times New Roman, 10" text.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxFNTP_USEFONT_FOR_LABEL: Uses the currently selected font to draw the label of the button.

.RE

